text.div: No narrative is provided for definitional resources. A human-readable rendering can be found in the implementation guide(s) where this resource is used.

description.value: An anatomical location specifies the location (e.g. foot) and laterality (e.g. left) of a body part.

purpose.value: A derived profile from [zib-AnatomicalLocation-BodyStructure](http://nictiz.nl/fhir/StructureDefinition/zib-AnatomicalLocation-BodyStructure) to provide a version better suited for implementation purposes.
